WEBVTT

00:13.986 --> 00:16.209
Well, good morning, Calvary.

00:16.249 --> 00:19.713
So grateful to see you here in God's house together.

00:19.733 --> 00:28.705
This is going to be a special weekend as we celebrate 40 years of Calvary Chapel as a church, a generation of Jesus followers.

00:28.865 --> 00:33.571
And as all of our campuses join us to hear our origin story.

00:33.611 --> 00:36.695
There's something significant about the number 40.

00:37.616 --> 00:39.378
See, the Bible 40 is

00:39.906 --> 00:41.990
the length of time of the generation.

00:42.050 --> 00:52.448
We see this as we go through the journey of 1 Samuel, Eli, rain for 40 years, and then Samuel for 40, and then Saul for 40, and then David for 40, and then Solomon for 40.

00:53.129 --> 01:01.023
We're going to take a pause from the book of 1 Samuel this weekend just to talk about the significance of that number 40 in the life of our church and the life of the people of God.

01:02.064 --> 01:03.026
You're going to hear

01:03.170 --> 01:04.011
our origin story.

01:04.031 --> 01:07.895
If you're new to Calvary, then this is going to be the first time you've heard this origin story.

01:07.915 --> 01:18.185
And if you've been here for a while, they're going to be part of the story that you probably didn't know because we've been left this beautiful legacy of the people who went before us.

01:18.905 --> 01:22.389
And a legacy is just something that you leave to the next generation.

01:23.129 --> 01:32.178
And sometimes that legacy, well, they're tangible things like the seat you're sitting in, the campus you're at, the building you're at, that was, it was prayed over and

01:32.258 --> 01:36.043
invested in and paid for by a previous generation, and we have the benefit of that.

01:37.204 --> 01:43.533
But it's not just the tangible parts of a legacy that spiritual fathers and mothers leave, there's the intangible.

01:44.534 --> 02:00.114
You think about maybe what your parents left you as a legacy, not just the stuff, but that courage to take risks or the desire to pray when things were bigger than the resilience when things didn't go well, or that fear sense of hope like we need in this moment,

02:00.226 --> 02:03.730
that was passed on to you to say, no matter what happens, I can look up.

02:03.750 --> 02:17.084
And we've been given this incredible and tangible legacy, the spirit of the people of Calvary that believe deeply in the gospel, that go after the one that believe we are better together, that believe this idea of generosity brings joy.

02:17.104 --> 02:20.687
This is the ethos, the DNA of the people of God that went before us.

02:20.707 --> 02:23.390
And we have this beautiful benefit at this moment.

02:23.410 --> 02:27.154
And so we're going to go on this 40-day journey together.

02:27.650 --> 02:30.554
And it's gonna be a journey of prayer and a journey of generosity.

02:30.594 --> 02:37.303
As you received this vision guide when you walked in at your campus, we're gonna ask you over these next 40 days to begin to pray.

02:37.344 --> 02:42.431
What does it mean for me to invest in the vision of Calvary Chapel for the next 40 years?

02:42.471 --> 02:43.712
And we'll talk more about that.

02:43.732 --> 02:51.243
We're gonna go through this moment of prayer where we pray for the next 40 days, these prayer cards that are available at all of our campuses for you to pick up.

02:51.724 --> 02:53.426
If you want a digital version of that,

02:53.538 --> 02:59.786
Well, you can scan the QR code, the code that's on the screen behind me, or your campus, and you're gonna get those digital prayer cards.

03:00.166 --> 03:03.370
There's gonna be prayer meetings that are gonna happen over these 40 days at your campuses.

03:03.931 --> 03:15.085
There's gonna be a chance to watch the Jesus revolution, because that's part of our origin storage, and see how the gospel spread all over the nation, 40, 50, 60 years ago, and how it's come to us.

03:16.006 --> 03:19.630
And so we're excited to be on this journey in our prayer to God.

03:19.971 --> 03:22.514
Is God what you did in this first generation of Calvary?

03:23.074 --> 03:23.554
Do it again.

03:24.375 --> 03:28.700
So let's take a moment and pray and ask God to do it only He can do.

03:29.461 --> 03:30.141
Let's pray together.

03:32.003 --> 03:36.428
Father, we thank You for this powerful word that You give us in the Bible.

03:38.229 --> 03:50.482
Remember that when we remember, when we look back, we don't just live in nostalgia, but we learn about the faith and the risk and the sacrifice

03:51.298 --> 04:01.390
And the attitude that shaped the people who went before us, their faith in you, Jesus, and how they lived their life, and how that can cause us to live in a different way today.

04:01.470 --> 04:19.452
So God, I pray that you would speak to us through your words, through your origin story of this place, and that we would be on this mission to make disciples with a whole new, passionate desire that you would awaken us to see the revival that's right in front of us, and that we would lean into that moment.

04:20.373 --> 04:21.234
Let me pray this.

04:21.570 --> 04:22.251
In Jesus' name.

04:23.693 --> 04:23.953
Amen.

04:26.236 --> 04:28.980
You know, the story of God has always been bigger than us.

04:30.602 --> 04:36.069
Sometimes in life, we make all that we read in the Bible about us, but we entered into a story that was already happening.

04:36.971 --> 04:45.061
God is writing a story from the beginning of time and history all the way through this present moment and into the future, and we've been invited into this story.

04:45.081 --> 04:48.346
And as we read the Bible, the Bible is not just one book.

04:48.386 --> 04:51.570
The Bible is actually 66 different books.

04:52.034 --> 05:11.744
66 different stories written by 40 authors over 1500 years, over three continents, and each of these individual books all tell the same story, pointing to the God who created everything, the God who went on mission, Father, Son, and Spirit to save us in our brokenness.

05:12.885 --> 05:16.050
And now that story has come to us, and maybe you've never

05:16.482 --> 05:19.907
wondered, like, how did the story of thousands of years ago get to us?

05:19.927 --> 05:25.595
How is it that we're sitting here in church watching online and hearing a story that's thousands of years old?

05:25.655 --> 05:28.339
Well, I want to tell you that origin story.

05:29.541 --> 05:38.354
And to do that, I want to walk over to this bookshelf and I want to pull off the book of Psalms, one of the 66 books of the Bible.

05:39.234 --> 05:43.278
And the Psalms talk about one generation declaring God's work to the next.

05:43.298 --> 05:46.921
That there's this spiritual legacy that's passed from one generation to the next.

05:46.961 --> 05:52.246
And one of those Psalms, Psalms 78, was written by the worship leader of Israel.

05:52.307 --> 05:53.328
His name was Asaph.

05:54.188 --> 05:57.792
And Asaph was passionate about teaching the people of God through song.

05:58.152 --> 06:00.575
This is your story.

06:01.676 --> 06:08.402
And so let's listen to the words of this 3000 year old song and let Asaph teach us how faith is passed

06:08.578 --> 06:10.020
from one generation to the next.

06:10.922 --> 06:13.506
He says, oh, my people, listen to my instructions.

06:14.407 --> 06:19.455
Open your ears to what I'm saying, for I will speak to you in a parable.

06:20.136 --> 06:27.768
I will teach you hidden lessons from our past, stories we have heard and known, stories our ancestors handed down to us.

06:28.589 --> 06:30.532
We will not hide these truths from our children.

06:31.133 --> 06:37.042
We will tell the next generation about the glorious deeds of the Lord, about His power and His mighty wonders.

06:37.506 --> 06:39.148
For he issued his laws to Jacob.

06:39.849 --> 06:41.411
He gave his instructions to Israel.

06:42.192 --> 06:50.582
He commanded our ancestors to teach them to their children so the next generation might know them, even the children not yet born.

06:51.583 --> 06:54.446
And they in turn will teach their own children.

06:54.466 --> 07:04.178
So each generation should set its hope anew on God, not forgetting his glorious miracles and obeying his commands.

07:05.634 --> 07:08.838
What is this worship leader of Israel teaching the people back then?

07:08.858 --> 07:10.240
And what is he teaching us today?

07:10.300 --> 07:14.525
That every generation has to set its hope anew in God.

07:14.825 --> 07:19.892
It's not enough to know your grandparents or great grandparents or parents, how to faith in God, a faith in Jesus.

07:19.972 --> 07:25.178
No, it's the responsibility of every generation to tell the stories, not to hide them.

07:25.198 --> 07:28.022
This is how God saved me, how God drew me.

07:28.042 --> 07:31.346
And ASAP says, this is a parable.

07:32.386 --> 07:35.632
A parable is an earthly story with a heavenly meaning.

07:35.692 --> 07:47.254
Every time you tell the story of what happened to you in life and how God met you and forgave you and saved you and put you on a mission, you tell a greater story of a God in heaven who's also on a mission.

07:48.476 --> 07:51.502
And it's powerful to think about the idea this song came to us.

07:53.285 --> 07:54.388
But how did it come to us?

07:54.408 --> 07:55.730
I mean, this was written so

07:56.226 --> 08:04.620
Long ago, well, as people faithfully told the story of God and taught the songs of God, well, this story came to a young man named John.

08:05.842 --> 08:16.239
John was a young Jewish teenager, and he was waiting for the promise of Messiah, that God would send his own son, that God would come from heaven to earth.

08:16.319 --> 08:23.090
And one day, well, John is hanging out with his friends and he hears about this man named Jesus.

08:24.386 --> 08:26.429
And John asked Jesus, hey, where are you staying?

08:26.449 --> 08:27.791
And Jesus says, come and see.

08:27.831 --> 08:29.594
And John goes on this great adventure.

08:29.634 --> 08:33.379
He leaves his father's business and begins to follow Jesus.

08:33.419 --> 08:37.385
And he hears some of these moments that we still talk about today.

08:37.405 --> 08:49.764
He wrote down this conversation that Jesus had with Nicodemus where Jesus said, God so loved the world that he gave his one and only son, that whoever believes him doesn't have to perish, but they can have everlasting life.

08:50.725 --> 08:54.130
Jesus got to hear, or John got to hear Jesus say,

08:54.914 --> 08:59.900
as the Father has sent me, now I send you, and you're gonna do greater things that I have done.

08:59.940 --> 09:04.385
And in this world, you're gonna have trouble, but take heart, I have overcome the world.

09:05.426 --> 09:21.544
And John experienced this life which he wrote it all down, and the last sentence of his story, of his gospel, the last sentence of his narrative of Jesus' life is one of my favorite lines in all the Bible.

09:22.725 --> 09:23.666
At 90 years old,

09:24.098 --> 09:26.561
John is the only disciple left.

09:28.224 --> 09:35.073
And he reflects on all that Jesus had done and all that he saw people doing in and through the life of Jesus.

09:35.133 --> 09:38.798
And he wrote this, and Jesus did many other things as well.

09:39.039 --> 09:48.151
And if every one of them were written down, I suppose that even the whole world would not have room for the books that would be written.

09:50.074 --> 09:52.978
It's like John is scratching his head going, man,

09:53.570 --> 10:04.067
I remember this and I remember that and I've written out so much, but there's so much more to tell about what he did and the stories that would be written that the people who follow Jesus that put their faith in trust and would continue to tell that story.

10:04.087 --> 10:11.278
There would be this unbroken relay between the gospel, the good news of God coming to the world and us.

10:12.641 --> 10:16.988
And those stories that were written, well, there's another book of the Bible, another story.

10:17.008 --> 10:18.450
It's called the book of Acts.

10:18.914 --> 10:25.681
And the book of Acts describes ordinary people filled with the Spirit of God who did what they did in a way that changed the world forever.

10:27.323 --> 10:29.505
You see, Jesus didn't just teach His disciples.

10:31.007 --> 10:39.496
He didn't just give them this great commission, go and make disciples, go baptize people in the name of the Father, Son, the Spirit, and teach them to obey everything I've commanded.

10:40.757 --> 10:45.362
He told them to wait in Jerusalem so they could receive power, Acts 1 8.

10:45.698 --> 10:55.034
Jesus said, you will receive power when the Holy Spirit comes on you, and you will be by witnesses in Jerusalem and in Judea and Samaria and to the ends of the earth.

10:56.397 --> 11:02.788
How do these first Christians have the courage to speak into a world that would curse them and persecute them and martyr them?

11:03.589 --> 11:05.212
They were filled with the Spirit of God.

11:06.154 --> 11:07.937
Acts chapter 2 describes this moment.

11:07.957 --> 11:08.658
They were praying.

11:08.678 --> 11:10.802
They were huddled in Jerusalem.

11:11.138 --> 11:16.405
All of a sudden, the sound of a mighty rushing wind and tongues of fire over their heads.

11:16.425 --> 11:22.072
And they spoke in languages that shared the gospel of all languages all around Jerusalem.

11:22.093 --> 11:23.194
And then Peter stands up.

11:23.234 --> 11:26.598
Peter, the guy who just weeks before denied, he even knew who Jesus was.

11:27.820 --> 11:32.306
Peter stands up and he tells the story that Asaph was talking about.

11:32.706 --> 11:36.391
The story of David, the story of the prophets, the story of God's faithfulness.

11:36.431 --> 11:51.870
Talking about how one generation to the next was looking for Messiah, and then he says, in that Jesus, he has come, but he was crucified, but death could not hold him, and he was raised from death to life, and if you repent and believe, well, here's what he says.

11:52.811 --> 12:01.842
You can repent and be baptized every one of you in the name of Jesus Christ for the forgiveness of your sins, and you'll receive the gift of the Holy Spirit.

12:02.466 --> 12:11.424
The promise is for you and your children, and for all who are far off, for all whom the Lord our God will call.

12:11.525 --> 12:16.014
And 3,000 people this day put their faith and trust in Jesus.

12:16.034 --> 12:19.381
Can we just celebrate that moment in our history, our origin story?

12:21.024 --> 12:23.890
That the first sermon by a fisherman

12:24.770 --> 12:32.300
who was afraid to even say he knew who Jesus was, now stands in boldness, and 3,000 people respond in one day.

12:33.803 --> 12:36.426
But here's the coolest part to me of this story.

12:37.748 --> 12:45.939
This gift of God's spirit, this gift of the story he's entrusted to us, of the gospel, isn't just for the people Peter was preaching to.

12:45.979 --> 12:53.650
Notice this promises for their children and their children after them and those who are far off, which means that promise has come,

12:55.010 --> 12:55.411
to us.

12:57.473 --> 12:58.875
Just let that sink in for a second.

12:59.616 --> 13:10.912
The first sermon in the book of Acts has us in mind that this gospel story and the power of God's spirit working through ordinary people has come to us and it's our turn to pass our faith on to the next generation.

13:12.034 --> 13:15.719
But now you might wonder, well, how did the gospel get to us from this moment?

13:15.739 --> 13:21.307
And that would be a very good question, which brings me to my next book, my next story.

13:21.327 --> 13:23.730
It's a story of church history.

13:25.186 --> 13:30.732
And I want to tell this to you like story time with Uncle Doug, so let's sit down and have a conversation.

13:31.393 --> 13:32.414
But have you ever been curious?

13:33.835 --> 13:38.580
How did the Christian faith, this fierce hope in who Jesus is and the power of the resurrection?

13:38.600 --> 13:39.501
How did it come to us?

13:40.522 --> 13:44.006
Well, let's trace our origin story and let's see what we can discover.

13:44.046 --> 13:51.474
In 34 A.D., Paul encounters Jesus on the road to the Damascus and his life is transformed.

13:52.802 --> 13:59.070
In 48 AD, Paul begins his first missionary journey, taking the gospel to the world.

14:00.411 --> 14:03.675
In 280 AD, churches begin to emerge in northern Italy.

14:05.137 --> 14:08.901
In 596 AD, Augustine brings the gospel to England.

14:10.283 --> 14:16.691
In 1517, Martin Luther posts his 95 theses on the church door at Wittenberg, and their reformation begins.

14:18.052 --> 14:22.738
In 1735, John and Charles Wesley traveled from England to America to preach

14:23.266 --> 14:23.867
the gospel.

14:25.228 --> 14:30.313
In 1784, the Methodist Church flourishes through preachers who travel by horseback.

14:31.834 --> 14:41.984
In 1886, the Parham family plants a church and a Bible college that will influence a man named Will Seymour.

14:42.004 --> 14:52.434
In 1906, Seymour begins revival meetings in Los Angeles, resulting in the Azusa Street Revival, attracting an evangelist named Amy McPherson.

14:53.602 --> 14:59.608
In 1923, McPherson helps found four square church and life Bible college.

15:00.990 --> 15:06.316
In 1948, Chuck Smith graduates from life Bible college.

15:07.277 --> 15:16.947
And in 1965, Chuck Smith begins pastoring a church of 25 people called Calvary Chapel in Costa Mesa, California.

15:18.349 --> 15:19.069
We could celebrate that.

15:19.109 --> 15:22.113
That's a, we're even closer to our, our own.

15:22.373 --> 15:23.474
In 1968,

15:23.714 --> 15:28.500
Smith partners with an 18-year-old evangelist Lonnie Frisbee in the Jesus movement is born.

15:29.662 --> 15:37.332
Through the 1970s, hundreds of Calvary Chapel churches are planted across the United States, including Las Vegas, Nevada.

15:38.374 --> 15:46.405
In 1980, Bob Coy begins attending Calvary Chapel Las Vegas and senses the call of God to plant a church in Fort Lauderdale, Florida.

15:47.226 --> 15:53.234
Yeah, and Bob and Diane moved there with Fidel and Theresa Gomez and their young family.

15:54.658 --> 15:58.863
And here we go, in 1985, 40 years ago.

15:59.724 --> 16:07.755
The first church service of Calvary Chapel Fort Lauderdale is held in a small hotel room with seven people in attendance.

16:08.796 --> 16:11.760
You have got to be kidding me, right?

16:11.800 --> 16:14.403
This is how the gospel got to us.

16:14.423 --> 16:18.048
Now, to tell the story of the next 40 years, well, I don't want to read it to you.

16:18.148 --> 16:19.049
I want you to watch it.

16:19.269 --> 16:23.154
And I want you to watch it through the eyes of two of our original

16:23.234 --> 16:26.119
founders and leaders of this church, Rod and Don Piercy.

16:26.139 --> 16:28.945
Take a look at their story.

16:28.965 --> 16:30.387
I grew up in Las Vegas, Nevada.

16:31.129 --> 16:33.854
Early on, I got a real interest in music.

16:34.976 --> 16:36.739
Music was everything in the 60s.

16:37.661 --> 16:47.058
Getting ready to go into college, I had a really deep experience with the Lord and always found a way to be able to go and serve the Lord with my music.

16:47.138 --> 16:50.903
Some friends of mine had already started Calvary Chapel Las Vegas.

16:50.923 --> 17:00.016
One of the guys there was our founding pastor here at Calvary Chapel for Lauderdale, Bob Coy, and we both needed a roommate and so we moved in together.

17:00.416 --> 17:09.168
Just a year later, Bob and Diane received the call from the Lord really to come out and start Calvary Chapel for Lauderdale.

17:09.188 --> 17:10.450
I came to visit

17:10.530 --> 17:12.313
They wanted to start doing some outreaches.

17:12.453 --> 17:17.221
Back in 85, spring break was still huge for Lutterdale.

17:18.524 --> 17:27.098
They rented a little community meeting room in Howard Johnson's, down on A1A, and called the recovery room.

17:28.360 --> 17:36.594
And we would offer all the drunk kids free sandwiches in Walksa Guy, and he has actually got

17:36.738 --> 17:41.624
a styrofoam cooler with the neck cut out on his head.

17:41.944 --> 17:47.230
He's standing right in front of us as we're saying, praise the Lord, praise the Lord.

17:47.810 --> 17:52.175
And we've got Mr. Styrofoam head right here in front of us.

17:52.195 --> 18:00.365
So after Bob and Diane moved out here, my sister and brother-in-law were helping start a church in Southern California.

18:00.905 --> 18:05.170
So I was traveling down to lead worship on the weekends.

18:05.634 --> 18:11.040
My friend Bobby met Rod and just liked him right away when we met each other finally.

18:11.541 --> 18:14.604
It's like, oh, it was not love at first sight, that was for sure.

18:15.726 --> 18:18.709
I said, hey, I'll call you.

18:19.410 --> 18:24.916
That's really how I got to learn who he is and falling in love with him over the phone.

18:24.956 --> 18:28.981
Eventually he moved there and then he asked me to marry him.

18:29.001 --> 18:31.684
It was really a fantastic time in our lives.

18:32.005 --> 18:33.266
We were as happy as could be.

18:33.986 --> 18:45.645
In 1995, I got a call from my brother-in-law, Clay Hecox, who had come to be the worship leader here at Calvary Chapel Fort Lauderdale.

18:45.665 --> 18:49.691
And he said, the church has more than tripled in size.

18:49.851 --> 18:51.073
I need help.

18:51.354 --> 18:53.858
Would you finally consider coming?

18:53.878 --> 18:54.919
Oh, no.

18:55.140 --> 18:55.921
That's not for us.

18:55.981 --> 18:56.562
We were

18:56.898 --> 18:58.662
He was working, going to school.

18:58.782 --> 18:59.684
He was working.

18:59.704 --> 19:01.809
He was doing worship at the church that we were in.

19:01.829 --> 19:05.157
We loved visiting, but there was never a desire to be here.

19:05.197 --> 19:09.126
And so when we were asked, we were like, oh no, I don't think so, but we will pray about it.

19:09.808 --> 19:14.418
There was really four big things, four big reasons where we thought.

19:15.586 --> 19:16.827
No, we can't go.

19:17.027 --> 19:23.814
And to make a very long story shorter, all four of those things God resolved within two weeks time.

19:24.054 --> 19:31.461
At that point, Don and I looked at each other and said, uh-oh, we're going to Fort Lauderdale.

19:35.665 --> 19:44.594
If I was really honest, I would have to say that there was this lack of the fulfillment of a call in my life.

19:44.770 --> 20:00.068
And so when we got that call from Fort Lauderdale and got answered all four of those big things that we didn't think he would be answering, we realized for the first time together as a couple, God's calling in our life.

20:02.271 --> 20:08.758
So when we came in 1995, we knew that the church had just experienced exponential growth.

20:10.881 --> 20:12.082
That didn't stop.

20:12.194 --> 20:14.625
that kept happening and kept happening.

20:15.509 --> 20:16.333
It was just crazy.

20:16.353 --> 20:21.778
It was like, you know, no matter what we did, people were coming, you know, and it just felt like, like,

20:22.018 --> 20:24.201
God was just on the move and we were just trying to keep up.

20:24.221 --> 20:28.367
When we had a big heart for outreach, we would do the stadium services.

20:28.467 --> 20:30.751
That was an amazing thing when we first got here.

20:30.831 --> 20:35.638
And we would just see people come from all walks of life, almost like a revival in some ways.

20:36.158 --> 20:41.786
People in business suits, to bikers, people in flip flops and shorts just come out of the ocean.

20:41.846 --> 20:49.938
We absolutely loved it because there was a freedom and an excitement for what God was going to do next.

20:53.794 --> 20:55.116
I love this picture of you.

20:55.396 --> 21:00.964
I don't know, it just makes me remember how, you know, you leading the show.

21:00.984 --> 21:01.505
How good looking I was.

21:01.525 --> 21:04.509
You were very good.

21:04.529 --> 21:05.651
You liked the cowboys.

21:05.991 --> 21:08.314
I do, yeah.

21:08.334 --> 21:16.586
The beautiful thing that was happening was that people were confident that they were gonna hear the gospel if they brought their friends.

21:17.127 --> 21:19.790
Now the stage was a lot lower in those days.

21:19.810 --> 21:22.354
A much more intimate

21:22.434 --> 21:30.346
environment where we really felt like we were part of those people's experience when they surrendered their heart to the Lord.

21:30.866 --> 21:44.887
I love that that continues at our church today, that no matter who gives the invitation, if Doug gives the invitation or any one of our guest teachers, the spirit of the Lord has been upon us for all these years.

21:46.749 --> 21:49.874
Being in ministry isn't always getting up

21:50.114 --> 21:56.060
to the sound of worship music and having God speak a special song in your ear every day.

21:57.141 --> 22:01.665
Don and I went through some very hard times and we wanted to run.

22:02.226 --> 22:12.075
When there were times in my life where I felt like I had failed miserably, God spoke into my life and says, your giftings and your calling remained the same.

22:13.076 --> 22:18.962
There were times in this ministry that we all went through some really deep dark

22:19.106 --> 22:20.228
painful times.

22:20.808 --> 22:26.056
It came to light that our founding pastor had fallen.

22:26.958 --> 22:32.786
I was thrust into the presidency for our church.

22:33.227 --> 22:37.593
I was president for five weeks and it was five excruciating weeks.

22:38.314 --> 22:41.859
It was painful every step of the way.

22:42.240 --> 22:46.386
God had me at that time for that season, for that reason.

22:46.690 --> 22:48.972
We thought, this is the end of the ministry.

22:48.992 --> 22:49.553
This is over.

22:49.893 --> 22:51.134
It's going to crash and burn.

22:51.735 --> 22:52.856
And it didn't.

22:52.876 --> 22:58.321
God came through and gave us the leaders that we have now, gave us the church that we have now.

22:58.641 --> 23:02.465
I really attribute that to the fact that Jesus called us deeply.

23:02.905 --> 23:05.608
We served Him deeply and we will continue to.

23:07.229 --> 23:16.498
Watching a person change from non-belief to belief, from being separated from God to being united with God.

23:16.898 --> 23:21.142
Watching that moment is the miracle moment for me.

23:21.162 --> 23:23.304
Our prayer is, God, please do it again.

23:23.765 --> 23:24.906
Bring more people to you.

23:25.386 --> 23:31.672
Bring more people to you in a way, Lord, where we feel like we're doing what the Bible calls the Great Commission.

23:31.712 --> 23:35.336
That's what I think of when I hear God do it again.

23:35.356 --> 23:37.398
It's been an amazing adventure.

23:37.818 --> 23:39.420
He's got us on mountains.

23:39.440 --> 23:40.420
He's got us in valleys.

23:41.081 --> 23:43.844
And everywhere along the way, he meets us.

23:43.864 --> 23:46.226
And I'm so thankful to be part

23:46.562 --> 23:49.087
even in the challenges, even in the difficult times.

23:50.169 --> 23:51.712
And so it's been really a beautiful thing.

23:51.772 --> 23:53.455
And, you know, it's not over yet.

23:53.896 --> 23:54.758
Journey's not over yet.

23:55.078 --> 23:55.940
Still an adventure.

23:56.721 --> 23:59.867
And we're looking forward to seeing what he does and how he does it.

24:00.328 --> 24:01.330
We just want to be part.

24:09.474 --> 24:13.701
One generation declares the works of God to the next.

24:13.721 --> 24:15.664
They tell of his mighty deeds.

24:15.704 --> 24:20.030
And the story of Calvary Chapel is not about all these perfect people who did all these perfect things.

24:20.111 --> 24:25.178
It's about a faithful God that even when we fell, he picked this back up because this church belongs to him.

24:25.559 --> 24:26.781
And we celebrate that.

24:29.485 --> 24:31.809
And he's still working.

24:31.829 --> 24:37.778
And so our prayer in this next season, well, it comes from this final book on the bookshelf,

24:38.370 --> 24:47.500
It's the book of Habakkuk, a prophet who wanted to see God work, but was in the middle of crisis and chaos.

24:48.441 --> 24:50.723
Mostly a moment like this where you're like, what's going to happen next?

24:51.064 --> 24:51.784
I don't know.

24:51.804 --> 24:57.991
In Habakkuk, well, he prayed this prayer as he wrestled with God.

24:59.072 --> 25:03.217
He said, Lord, I've heard of your fame and I stand in awe of your deeds.

25:03.237 --> 25:08.242
Lord, repeat them in our day, in our time, make

25:08.418 --> 25:09.860
them known.

25:11.202 --> 25:14.827
God, I've heard the stories of what you did back then.

25:15.669 --> 25:18.793
I've heard of your fame, the way you did all these things for your people.

25:19.454 --> 25:24.782
They've been passed on to me from the previous generation, but I don't want to just hear stories and live in nostalgia.

25:25.002 --> 25:30.751
I want to see it with my own eyes, renew your powerful works in our day so I can see them with my own eyes.

25:31.011 --> 25:32.634
God, do it again.

25:32.674 --> 25:38.322
And this has become our prayer for this next season.

25:38.850 --> 25:43.417
God placed this verse and this part of the story in my heart almost a year ago.

25:44.639 --> 25:51.109
And I would wake up and I would look around and say, God, you've done some amazing things in our life in Suzanne and my life in our family.

25:51.129 --> 25:54.774
You've done some amazing things in our church and in our campuses, but God, would you do it again?

25:54.874 --> 25:57.959
What you did in the past do it in bigger and greater ways.

25:57.999 --> 26:00.022
We want to see it with our own eyes.

26:01.204 --> 26:05.590
And so I want that to be our anthem at all of our campuses, all that you know is Calvary Chapel.

26:06.011 --> 26:07.954
I want us to every day wake up and say, Lord,

26:09.026 --> 26:09.506
Do it again.

26:10.768 --> 26:13.530
One generation commends the works of God to the next.

26:13.631 --> 26:16.994
Our kids and the next generation needs to hear the stories of God's faithfulness.

26:17.014 --> 26:19.136
So we're going to practice this today.

26:19.296 --> 26:22.499
I'm going to say, Lord, and you're going to say, do it again.

26:22.539 --> 26:23.781
Lord.

26:25.322 --> 26:26.183
Now, here's the question.

26:26.323 --> 26:27.564
What has he done?

26:27.604 --> 26:29.626
Let's just take a moment and talk about what he's done.

26:30.327 --> 26:37.394
Since those seven people met in that little hotel room 40 years ago, a generation ago, listen to this.

26:37.666 --> 26:42.212
60,000 people have given their life to Jesus, made a decision to follow Jesus.

26:42.232 --> 26:44.976
60,000, and that's the best we can count.

26:44.996 --> 26:54.769
30,000 people have been baptized during that time, and we wanna celebrate that, and we wanna say, Lord, do it again.

26:55.810 --> 27:04.562
Now, just show of hands, whatever campus you're at, wherever you're sitting, if you were saved here, you made a decision to follow Jesus, or you were baptized here at the church, I want you to raise your hand.

27:04.962 --> 27:06.284
All right, everyone look around, guys.

27:06.424 --> 27:11.610
It's a room full of people whose lives have been transformed by the gospel of Jesus.

27:11.710 --> 27:32.594
And again, as we flash back, I want you just to watch these early pictures, these early stories of how he did it, starting in a funeral home and then eventually going to a school and then to an Albertson, right behind it, Albertson's in a little mall and then to Gateway and this passionate worship, this invite, my wife and I were invited to Calvary Chapel so many times,

27:33.026 --> 28:02.546
stadium services and baptisms and people knowing the joy of life with Jesus, the relationship with Jesus changes everything, people spilling out into the streets and campuses being formed all across South Florida and missions being planted and we look at all those things and we're like, God, God, do it again and let that again be our prayer as its people and not just here but in the first generation of Calvary,

28:02.946 --> 28:04.489
We saw all these people give their life to you.

28:04.569 --> 28:14.567
In the first generation of Calvary, listen, we were able to plant 34 churches all around South Florida and all around the United States of America.

28:14.968 --> 28:23.684
And that's a beautiful, a beautiful legacy to know that these churches, we can't even measure the impact of those churches and 24 churches globally.

28:23.724 --> 28:26.770
So all around the world, 58 churches

28:26.850 --> 28:29.813
are now meeting, sharing the gospel, doing all that stuff.

28:30.254 --> 28:33.277
And we know that God wants to do even more.

28:33.377 --> 28:37.962
So our prayer is God, do it again, not just that.

28:38.843 --> 28:49.834
But because of the generosity of this church, this church has given $75 million to local outreach and global missions in its history in 40 years.

28:51.396 --> 28:53.618
And we work with 130

28:53.730 --> 29:01.566
one partners both here and around the world to bring the gospel, the good news of Jesus to those who are in desperate need.

29:01.586 --> 29:07.858
And this again is the legacy, the intangible legacy that God has given us here at Calvary.

29:08.770 --> 29:14.285
In the first generation of Calvary, we started a school called Calvary Christian Academy.

29:14.305 --> 29:24.392
An idea that a school could be focused not just on great academics or great sports or STEM programs or arts, but making disciples, a focus on the mission that Jesus gave us.

29:24.492 --> 29:25.074
And listen,

29:25.282 --> 29:40.942
To this day, 2,527 students have graduated from this school as world changers, and we have seen four campuses of CCA emerge, and our prayer is, God, do it again.

29:41.002 --> 29:53.938
But you know, before we started that school in the early 2000s, we hit pause on the idea of a school because there were kids in foster care, sleeping in office buildings.

29:54.850 --> 30:00.244
And we said before we build a school for kids that have, let's find a home for kids that don't.

30:00.264 --> 30:02.930
And so a ministry called For Kids began.

30:02.990 --> 30:08.043
And it was this grand vision, a Christian home for every child.

30:09.106 --> 30:10.770
And now years later,

30:11.106 --> 30:15.813
6,300 kids have found homes in Christian families.

30:16.133 --> 30:29.713
945 of them have been adopted permanently into those families, and over 2,000 have been reunited with their family as the churches come around those families, and we say, God, do it again.

30:29.773 --> 30:41.010
In this first generation, God has done so much, but we are leaning in to God, what if you did even more in the next generation?

30:41.186 --> 30:44.911
We just celebrated what God has done in 40 years, but I want to ask you this question.

30:46.913 --> 30:50.217
What if Calvary Chapel was never planted?

30:51.759 --> 30:55.003
What if those first few people never took those steps of faith?

30:55.043 --> 31:07.539
What if when we needed a bigger building, people didn't pray or give or vision, they just said, eh, how would your life be different if Calvary Chapel didn't exist?

31:09.841 --> 31:10.322
I mean,

31:11.746 --> 31:15.171
I think of Suzanne and I, coming here in 1998.

31:15.291 --> 31:24.904
I think of us, we were already Christians, we already knew Jesus, but we came here broken.

31:26.466 --> 31:28.689
We came here after the death of our son.

31:29.931 --> 31:34.678
We came here after a church that we're going to fell apart.

31:36.140 --> 31:40.626
We're going through after all the things we poured our lives into for Jesus turned out

31:41.250 --> 31:48.058
to all fall apart, and we just came here, and we just sat in worship, not at this property, but at the gateway property.

31:48.098 --> 31:49.179
We just cried.

31:50.701 --> 31:57.609
But there was something about the worship, the passion of the people, the teaching of God's word, the outwards that drew us in and healed us.

31:57.649 --> 32:01.293
And every time we saw someone come forward, there was something that brought us back to life.

32:02.895 --> 32:05.718
Suzanne and I came back to life because of Calvary Chapel.

32:06.760 --> 32:07.440
And not just that.

32:08.421 --> 32:08.882
Listen.

32:10.530 --> 32:25.169
When the doctors told us you shouldn't try to have another child because there's a one in three chances child's gonna be born with all these disabilities and we came forward and prayed with two elders right over here named Ron and Jeff.

32:26.351 --> 32:32.860
And we knew that God had healed our unborn child and Caden is now healthy today because of that moment right there because God answers prayers in this place.

32:32.900 --> 32:37.586
And we're sitting right over there when the vision was cast for four kids

32:37.730 --> 32:40.914
And we felt our hearts burn inside of our chest, and we knew God was calling us.

32:40.954 --> 32:54.510
So our jobs, our family photo, the things that happened as we adopted two kids, all those things wouldn't be the same if it wasn't for a previous generation who said yes to God, and the work of God's Spirit through them.

32:54.530 --> 32:56.892
This is the legacy that Suzanne and I have received.

32:57.934 --> 33:01.778
And as you think, and as you imagine, like, oh God,

33:01.890 --> 33:04.312
healed my marriage here or he healed my body here.

33:04.453 --> 33:06.955
He broke an addiction in my life here through the people of God.

33:07.376 --> 33:09.998
It's a beautiful, beautiful legacy to think about.

33:10.979 --> 33:20.849
And as we think about the intangible legacy of faith and sacrifice and generosity, we also think about the tangible gifts that this previous generation has given us.

33:20.929 --> 33:29.458
I mean, again, the seat you're sitting in, the building you're in, the online community, the VR room that you're in was all paid for by a previous generation.

33:30.498 --> 33:33.383
Their prayers, their sacrifices, their vision have given us what we have.

33:33.403 --> 33:36.568
And we don't want to be the people who don't think about that and just take it for granted.

33:36.588 --> 33:41.676
And we want to feel the weight of it and go, well, if they've been given all this to us, then what do we do with it?

33:41.696 --> 33:43.800
And so here's one of the coolest parts of this.

33:43.840 --> 33:47.145
I mean, you think about all that Calvary Chapel is today.

33:47.746 --> 33:53.516
And this summer, we paid off our mortgage so that everything that a Calvary Chapel has is debt-free.

33:53.756 --> 33:55.699
It's been paid in full by the first generation.

33:55.719 --> 33:57.362
And we celebrate.

33:57.666 --> 34:00.110
God's faithfulness through His people.

34:00.150 --> 34:15.874
So if you were part of that first generation, if you were part of those men and women with gray hair or no hair who've been here a long time and you've given your life and blood and sweat and tears and resources to make this happen, we want to say to you well done this first generation of God.

34:15.894 --> 34:20.721
Can we celebrate those men and women who have allowed us to be in this space?

34:22.744 --> 34:26.610
Ordinary people filled with the spirit of God.

34:26.818 --> 34:31.324
who had this deep passion that people could come to know Jesus.

34:32.605 --> 34:34.708
So what do we do with this?

34:34.748 --> 34:37.492
Well, our mission is the same to make disciples.

34:37.512 --> 34:41.937
Our vision is still broad to reach our community and to change our world.

34:42.017 --> 34:50.729
And well, I want to tell you how this group of men and women in these early days took these steps of faith.

34:50.749 --> 34:54.994
There would be a time where we'd be in a small group and then we needed more space and then we would

34:55.170 --> 35:22.066
go into a funeral home and they would rent a school, and then that was full, and now we had to rent this little area in this little shopping center, and then we ran out of space there, and parking there, and then we went to Gateway, and pretty soon we ran out of parking there, and ran out of space there for kids, and you watch people pull in, then pull out because there's no place, and we're like, we can't have that, and at every stage, people continued to pray and give, and in 1996, well, this property in Fort Lauderdale came on the market, and listen, it was $22 million.

35:22.086 --> 35:25.170
And you know how much Calvary Chapel had in the bank in 1996?

35:25.858 --> 35:26.238
400,000.

35:26.579 --> 35:28.500
Do the math.

35:29.822 --> 35:33.225
I know the guy at Bank of America who heard the pitch that said, hey, we want to buy this property.

35:33.245 --> 35:34.066
He laughed out loud.

35:35.267 --> 35:40.131
Because what kind of crazy people try to buy a $22 million property with $400,000 to the bank?

35:40.171 --> 35:40.412
I know.

35:40.752 --> 35:45.516
People who know that God is in control and that he wants to raise people with the gospel.

35:45.616 --> 35:49.900
And I want to show you one of the original visioners of this building in Fort Lauderdale.

35:50.281 --> 35:55.826
This was a guy I don't even know standing on a box talking about vision of what this space could be in 1997.

35:56.802 --> 35:59.265
Now, some people in that group, that guy's crazy.

35:59.305 --> 36:01.968
There's no way that that's gonna turn into this.

36:03.329 --> 36:06.713
But one generation tells the great work of God to the next generation.

36:06.733 --> 36:15.163
It happened and beyond what we could imagine as people gave generously to see something that would reach thousands of people with the gospel of Jesus.

36:15.523 --> 36:20.048
And not just here, but think about all the campuses that are part of this church family.

36:20.069 --> 36:24.914
Look at plantation, the plantation campus before it's the building you're sitting in the plantation.

36:25.250 --> 36:25.971
was just a field.

36:26.111 --> 36:27.514
And they didn't have 400,000.

36:27.674 --> 36:29.617
I said, hardly any money back.

36:29.637 --> 36:33.324
They came on Saturdays with chainsaws and cut down trees just to clear the land.

36:33.824 --> 36:39.334
People gave their own sweat and work because they believed that the mission of God was worth it.

36:39.414 --> 36:43.981
And this is the incredible legacy that we have been given.

36:45.123 --> 36:49.170
And we believe the time is now because in some of our campuses, we can't

36:49.570 --> 36:51.232
Find enough spaces to park people.

36:51.252 --> 36:52.913
There's not enough spaces for youth.

36:52.933 --> 36:55.436
We've watched our aging facilities sort of get up.

36:55.456 --> 36:58.719
We haven't done a vision campaign for over 20 years here at Calvary.

36:59.319 --> 37:06.446
We've just enjoyed this goodness of God as people faithfully give their ties and offerings and this beautiful thing has happened.

37:06.466 --> 37:15.074
But now we believe the time is now because even the events of this last week show us that the world is in desperate need of hope.

37:15.095 --> 37:18.738
And I want to show you the signs of what I call

37:18.850 --> 37:22.735
or what people are calling a quiet revival.

37:24.377 --> 37:30.924
I'm gonna show you what the Barnard Research Group has found as they've asked this question over the decades.

37:31.165 --> 37:35.490
The question is this, is a relationship with Jesus still important to you today?

37:35.550 --> 37:45.522
And in 2010, it reached its peak, 77% of people in America said a relationship with Jesus is important to me today, but then this precipitous decline

37:46.210 --> 38:04.854
to a right around COVID time where that dropped to 54% and prognosticators and theologians and pastors were worried, if this keeps going down, then Christianity and America is gonna be this dying thing and we're gonna end up like Europe, this post-Christian nation, except something unexpected happened after COVID.

38:05.715 --> 38:12.204
It suddenly began to tick back up and now 66% of people say a relationship with Jesus is important to me today.

38:13.345 --> 38:14.066
And do you know

38:14.306 --> 38:18.674
Who is driving this quiet revival?

38:20.034 --> 38:21.936
It's the young people in this country.

38:22.156 --> 38:31.445
It's Gen Z and Gen Alpha who are saying, all the stuff I'm seeing, all the hate I'm seeing, all the division I'm seeing, all the things that be you, do yourself, follow your heart.

38:31.545 --> 38:38.352
It's feeling so empty inside and I'm feeling the anxiousness and the depression of all this things that people are trying to sell me.

38:38.632 --> 38:44.658
I'm gonna put this down and I'm gonna pick this up and I'm gonna see, is there something that God has for me?

38:45.259 --> 38:48.402
And this is why we are

38:48.578 --> 38:53.688
So passionate about saying that the time is now these plans that we are about to show you.

38:53.768 --> 39:03.227
We've been laboring over and thinking over and praying over and we've had people look through surveys of buildings and most of these properties maybe you've never seen before.

39:03.267 --> 39:08.818
Maybe you've only seen the campus that you're in but I want you to know you're part of something way bigger than what you see with your eyes.

39:09.826 --> 39:11.547
So we wanna advocate for the vulnerable.

39:11.568 --> 39:14.590
We wanna see God do it again for those who are in need.

39:14.610 --> 39:16.652
We wanna raise the next generation.

39:16.712 --> 39:19.835
We see this rising awake in young people to know the gospel.

39:19.855 --> 39:25.159
And we wanna mobilize everyone in the church at every campus to say, I am on mission for Jesus.

39:25.279 --> 39:28.863
I'm not gonna let the despair and anger and fear of the world paralyze me.

39:28.923 --> 39:30.684
I'm gonna walk toward the mess.

39:30.704 --> 39:32.265
I'm gonna walk toward the confidence of Jesus.

39:32.366 --> 39:34.127
I'm not gonna fight evil with evil.

39:34.147 --> 39:35.108
I'm gonna fight evil with good.

39:35.148 --> 39:36.589
I'm gonna love my enemies.

39:36.609 --> 39:37.930
I'm gonna pray for my neighbors.

39:38.010 --> 39:39.812
I'm gonna go on mission for Jesus.

39:39.792 --> 39:47.563
So as you see these projects, I want you to think about the mission that happens in these spaces.

39:47.643 --> 39:52.611
So here at our Fort Lauderdale campus, we're looking for next-gen space.

39:52.691 --> 39:55.575
Our issue is not parking or sanctuary space necessarily.

39:55.615 --> 40:01.063
No, it's spaces for kids and youth to meet in small groups, to be discipled and sent out on mission.

40:01.083 --> 40:03.026
It's a youth room on this

40:03.138 --> 40:17.043
side of the property behind me and on our west campus, it's a warehouse that's being retrofitted as a student union of sorts of activities where youth can meet together, where they can do mission work together, where they can have time and space that's just for them.

40:18.045 --> 40:25.458
Our west campus, the old Fort Lauderdale Christian School property, well we have a plan and a dream to start a 700 student

40:25.570 --> 40:34.722
free K or K through third grade CCA, Calvary Christian Academy, to provide space for all of those young disciples of Jesus to come know him.

40:34.882 --> 40:42.011
And this will become the permanent home of Calvary Chapel Española as our Spanish campus has grown so much.

40:42.031 --> 40:44.153
There's not enough parking, there's not enough space.

40:44.434 --> 40:54.226
I mean, the place there are is threatening to tow cars now because there's so many cars coming because we have such a large Hispanic population in this

40:54.402 --> 40:56.164
region that needs to know Jesus.

40:56.244 --> 40:58.887
And some want to hear the gospel in their own language.

40:58.927 --> 41:02.751
And we want to see God do something powerful in that space.

41:02.791 --> 41:08.978
And our plantation campus, well, you already know, parking and kidspace is a real challenge and we see that.

41:09.018 --> 41:14.004
We don't want any cars to pull onto the property and pull off to say there's no space and room for me.

41:15.406 --> 41:16.727
Same thing with our Boca campus.

41:17.288 --> 41:20.872
Our Boca campus, we have very, very limited parking and kidspace.

41:21.152 --> 41:22.834
The youth meet in portables.

41:23.042 --> 41:29.108
And both the plantation campus and the Boca campus, we don't want to just build these spaces, these dreams for the campus.

41:29.148 --> 41:31.551
We want to start two more Christian schools.

41:31.891 --> 41:40.880
Again, Calvary Christian Academy schools, because our waiting list for this school is vast and people like, I want my kids to be discipled as Christians.

41:40.920 --> 41:46.426
And this is an opportunity to do both of those things at our plantation and Boca campus.

41:47.607 --> 41:48.628
Our West Boca campus?

41:49.189 --> 41:50.610
Well, it's in the Sandalford community.

41:51.394 --> 42:00.327
It's a very, very under-resourced community where kids, when they get off the bus, it's a very vulnerable space to go, is someone going to meet me at the bus stop?

42:00.387 --> 42:03.291
Are there people in this neighborhood who have bad intentions?

42:03.311 --> 42:05.915
Are there things that kids are going to get involved with?

42:06.536 --> 42:13.266
And our birthday gift for Jesus started an after-school program, and we want to provide some spaces in the backyard there for those kids to meet?

42:13.602 --> 42:21.390
We just hired the after-school coordinator and we can't wait to hear the stories of how in that neighborhood the gospel takes root in new ways.

42:21.751 --> 42:29.820
And then in our Boynton Beach campus, while our youth are meeting in a preschool hallway, not an ideal environment for young people to have their own space.

42:29.860 --> 42:39.570
We want our youth spaces to be the spaces where kids go, I want to invite my friends to this space because we're having this Bible study and it's the space that's inviting and we have the chance to do that.

42:39.682 --> 42:41.084
in Boynton as well.

42:41.124 --> 42:43.847
And then downtown Fort Lauderdale, we've been praying for a decade.

42:43.867 --> 42:52.536
God, is there a space in downtown Fort Lauderdale where we can have another plant for the gospel that people can drive by this church and say, you know, I didn't know there was a church in that neighborhood.

42:52.736 --> 42:55.139
Let me walk in and let me see what God is doing.

42:55.159 --> 43:01.526
Listen, tens of thousands of people are moving into the downtown region of Fort Lauderdale and they don't know Jesus.

